data.message:
Move kidash to a new directory.

This way it can be more easily covnerted into a pip package.
I included some minor changes to the rest to match this change.
[kidash] Add symbolic link to grimoire_elk so kidash can be executed without installing it.

[kidash] Add support for using panels in the panels module

Now, panels (JSON files with panel defintions) are looked for
first in a local directory panels/json, and if not found, in the
panels module, if it is present and importable.
For maintaining compatibility, panels with names such as
"panels/json/git.json" are supported. But the most simple
"git.json" is also supported, meaning "git.json" file in the
current directory, or "git.json" file in the corresponding
directory of the modules file.

See README.md for more details.

Versions for both grimoire-elk and grimoire-kidash are updated.

grimoirelab-panels is now a dependency of grimoire-kidash.

[kidash][setup] Fix dependency on panels package

panels is actually grimoirelab-panels.

[kidash] Add option to clean all items not included in data sources provided

There are panels like overview or data status that include all data
sources in them. But for a specific dashboard, only the active data sources
should be included. This is a first version that needs to be checked for
layout issues yet.
[kidash] Fix pep8 issues

[kidash] Unbundle kidash completely

This commit unbundles kidash completely from grimoire-elk.
Now, all of kidash lives in the kidash directory, and
everything should be ready to relocate in a standalone repo.
The kidash.py binary is now kidash, in the bin directory.
The pip package is now kidash.
Version now is 0.4.0 (it was 0.30.x with GrimoireELK, but
then it was grimoire-kidash, so this is really a new package).
[kidash] Fix error getting the title of an index pattern
[setup] Change to the new chaoss organization in GitHub
[flake8] Files now flake8 clean
Update version number to 0.4.1

[dashboard] Fix the bool filters for the dashboard

The 1/0 values are changed to True/False for kibana6 so the
filters work in this version.
[visualization] Include the style needed in Kibiana6 to show metrics vis correctly

[layout] Increase 1 height the panels of height 1 for kibana6

In kibana6 a panel with height 1 is too small to show the contents.
Merge branch 'kibana6-vis-metrics-height' of git://github.com/acs/grimoirelab-kidash
Merge branch 'acs-kibana6-vis-metrics-height'

[kidash] Remove by default from dashboards the study related visualizations

A new name convention exists in GrimoireLab panels
to allow kidash to decide if include the studies visualizations/widgets.
Study related widgets are named <source>_<study>_<name>, e.g.
'git_study_pair_programming_main_numbers'

There is a command line option to enable the importing of this studies:
--add-vis-studies
[release] Update version number to 0.4.2

[import] Don't modify the height of visualizatons in dashboards from Kibana >= 6

If a dashboard has been created with Kibana >= 6 the issue with the
height=1 in which the visualization can be shown completly because
the title bar has been shown. So don't modify the height in these
cases becasue the dashboard creator has decided to use this heigth=1
in any case.

Fixes #5

This code updates the import of the elastic class
[release] Update version number to 0.4.3

[kidash] Update elk import

[release] Update version number to 0.4.4
[kidash] Use #!/usr/bin/env python3 to work inside venvs correctly

[kidash] Preserve uiStateJSON dict when cleaning a dashboard from not needed data sources

In this dict is stored the custom title. It is just a state dict so if it includes
state related to panels that have been removed, it should not be a problem. Checked
that with the Overview panel.
[release] Update version number to 0.4.5

Add release_date to panel json

This change adds a new field `release_date` to panels exported using kidash. It also
adds a new `strict` argument that allows to upload a panel only when its release
date is newer than the one stored in `.kibana`.

Add try/except to show content of error responses

ElasticSearch returns error details within content. This change captures exceptions
from `kidash` binary and uses logger to print them.
Add constant for release date field name

Update mapping in Kibana6 if needed

When using Kibana 6, .kibana index mapping is set to strict. That means we cannot
include new fields in the index without explicitely add the corresponding mapping
for that field. This change detects when this error is raised, updates .kibana
mapping including `release_date`  field and tries to upload panel again.

[kidash] Add support for importing and exporting only index patterns

Added new option --split-index-patterns so the index patterns are stored
in separate files from the dashboard, visualization and searches.
[tests] Add test for split-index-patterns new param
[release] Update version number to 0.4.6

Add release date support for Index Patterns

Index patterns can be used in stritc mode now.
[release] Update version number to 0.4.7

Don't sys.exit from kidash.py library

All library must raise an exception if errors appear, never sys.exit because
it will exit the caller program. Let the caller program to manage the exception
and to decide what to do.
[release] Update version number to 0.4.8

[kidash] Remove dashboards by title

This code allows to remove dashboards by title, thus overcoming
the new way of generating ids in Kibana6, which are hashed-based.

Fix import/export of searches

`_id` checking for compatibility with old Kibana versions now
looks for type as prefix followed by `:` character. Old check
was wrong as it just checked if `_id` contained type in any
place, which is a problem because types are common words like
`search` that can be used as part of titles and ids as well.
Notice that old ids were not hashes, but string similar to
titles.

Add viz title to data source removal checks

GitLab visualizations weren't being added to Overview panel
when data source filtering is active. That was due to the use
of widget title in the checks, but not visualization title,
that is a different one. Widget's title is the one you set
in the dashboard, while the right one to use is the title you
set when creating the visualization, as it is hidden in the
dashboard and it doesn't change from dashboard to dashboard
as it is associated to the viz and not to the panel.

The old check using the title coming from the dashboard is
still there to avoid cases that could be already working based
on it.

[kidash] Support import to Kibiter/Kibana 6.8

This code allows to import Sigils dashboards to
Kibana/Kibiter 6.8.x instances, granting backward
compatibilty with previous versions.

Kibana 6.8.x sets the .kibana mapping to strict,
thus it makes impossible to modify the .kibana index
after creation. For this reason, Kidash has been modified
in the following way.

- Kidash now uploads an ad-hoc .kibana mapping, which
contains the metadashboard and projectname types. This
is needed to guarantee that Kibiter top menu works for
Kibana 6.8.x

- The `release_date` attribute stored in .kibana for
versions prior to 6.8.x has been moved to a different
index: `.grimoirelab-sigils`. This is needed since custom
fields cannot be saved in Kibana standard objects anymore
(dashboard, index patterns, etc.). Thus, each time there
is an attempt to upload a dashboard or index pattern to
Kibana, the release_date is retrieved from this new index
and compared with the release_date included in the
uploaded objects. If the object can be uploaed, the
release date included into it is popped out and saved
to the `.grimoirelab-sigils` index together with the
id and type of the object.

Signed-off-by: Valerio Cosentino <valcos@bitergia.com>
